{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 4:4Figure 4: Full UNETR architecture used in vipr.",
    "The base number of filters is set to M = 2P, where P is the number of output classes.",
    "The ViT encoder uses M attention heads and an embedding size of K = 512.",
    "In the CNN-based decoder, each convolutional block includes two instance normalization layers.",
    "Skip connections from selected transformer layers are integrated into the decoder to retain spatial context and support accurate volumetric segmentation."
  ]
}